[
<typeStatus id="E64F886AFFFBBE736E89FCF90EBE9CA8" box="[442,494,871,896]" pageId="17" pageNumber="461">type</typeStatus>
locality], Marianas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="394B36C8FFFBBE736F93FC350E049CED" blockId="17.[160,1155,939,1069]" box="[160,340,939,965]" pageId="17" pageNumber="461">
<emphasis id="0B80EADAFFFBBE736F93FC350E049CED" bold="true" box="[160,340,939,965]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="461">Ecological note</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="394B36C8FFFBBE736F93FC510E849B05" blockId="17.[160,1155,939,1069]" pageId="17" pageNumber="461">
<taxonomicName id="FEF44D4BFFFBBE736F93FC510E1E9CC0" authorityName="Naruse &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Ng" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[160,334,975,1000]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Circulium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="navus">
<emphasis id="0B80EADAFFFBBE736F93FC510E1E9CC0" box="[160,334,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="461">Circulium navus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been observed climbing coconut trees and 
<taxonomicName id="FEF44D4BFFFBBE736C5EFC510C899CC0" box="[877,985,975,1000]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="17" pageNumber="461" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0B80EADAFFFBBE736C5EFC510C899CC0" box="[877,985,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="461">Pandanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vines 
<quantity id="FE0C9B2DFFFBBE736B11FC510BD39CC0" box="[1058,1155,975,1000]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="461" unit="m" value="25.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="20.0">20–30 m</quantity>
from the sea, and in a few instances, near-vertical rocks at the base of large trees (
<bibRefCitation id="5D654B39FFFBBE736B03FC6C0E509B05" author="Ng PKL &amp; Liu HC" pageId="17" pageNumber="461" pagination="601 - 616" refId="ref44745" refString="Ng PKL, Liu HC. 2003. On a new species of tree-climbing crab of the genus Labuanium (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Sesarmidae) from Taiwan. Proc Biol Soc Wash. 116 (3): 601 - 616." type="journal article" year="2003">Ng and Liu 2003</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="FEF44D4BFFFBBE736E1FFB8A0E979B05" authorityName=": Ng and Liu" authorityYear="2003" box="[300,455,1044,1069]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Labuanium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="461" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundatum">
<emphasis id="0B80EADAFFFBBE736E1FFB8A0E979B05" box="[300,455,1044,1069]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="461">L. rotundatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
